# Ignore all checkpoints initially
checkpoint
# But we usually want to include specific ones, but .dockerignore whitelist is tricky.
# We will COPY them explicitly in Dockerfile from the source context.
# So we can ignore the root 'checkpoint' to prevent 'COPY .' from grabbing everything if we used that.
# However, if we do 'COPY checkpoint/ ...', it must be in the context.
# So we should NOT ignore checkpoint if we want to copy them.
# But we want to exclude unused checkpoints if there are many.
